<collectingCountry box="[314,429,1610,1635]" name="Sao Tome and Principe" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">São Tomé</collectingCountry>
, Rio de Janeiro, with an overall range from Espirito Santo to Rio de Janeiro states, 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1432,1610,1635]" name="Brazil" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, would apply here if they prove to be the same. Reported from 
<quantity box="[841,911,1647,1671]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="238" pageNumber="239" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
depth. Rios’ report (for 
<taxonomicName authority="Woodring, 1928" authorityName="Woodring" authorityYear="1928" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Syntomodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="238" pageNumber="239" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="espyra">
<emphasis box="[1181,1428,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="238" pageNumber="239">Syntomodrillia espyra</emphasis>
, Woodring, 
<number box="[276,333,1682,1707]" pageId="238" pageNumber="239" value="1928.0">1928</number>
</taxonomicName>
) indicates a possible depth range of 
<quantity box="[742,858,1683,1707]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="238" pageNumber="239" unit="m" value="72.5" valueMax="100.0" valueMin="45.0">
45– 
<specimenCount box="[785,862,1683,1707]" pageId="238" pageNumber="239" type="generic">100 m.</specimenCount>
</quantity>
</paragraph>
